news.title: Ibis to invest over Rs 500 crore to add four properties by FY24
news.para: ​Ibis, which last week opened its 20th property in the country at Vikroli in Mumbai offering 249 keys making it the largest, operates 3,808 rooms across 20 properties in 13 cities -- three of them in the megapolis alone -- in the country.

news.title: Asking prices for UK homes rise in unison for first time in 14 years
news.para: Average asking prices rose by 1.8% from a month earlier, the biggest jump at this time of year since 2015, to reach a record high of 344,445 pounds ($473,922).

news.title: CG Power to sell Kanjurmarg property to Evie Real Estate for Rs 382 crore
news.para: ​"As per the term sheet signed with the buyer (Evie Real Estate Pvt Ltd), the sale consideration has been fixed at Rs 382 crore, in addition to repayment of Rs 20 crore of deposit, under dispute. The transaction is scheduled to be completed on or before March 31, 2022 (long stop date)," according to a BSE filing.

news.title: Sabre Partners buys 13.4% stake in Aviom India Housing Finance
news.para: The lender, which doubled its asset under management to Rs 550 crore in a year, is aiming to grow its book to Rs 800 crore by March 2022.

news.title: Bengaluru development body to develop Rs 4,500 crore residential layout
news.para: The project is being monitored by a committee formed by the Supreme Court for its timely completion. Earlier this week, BDA approved the project cost in a board meeting. The authority plans to mobilise the revenue through its internal resources over the next three to four years.

news.title: UltraTech Cement's profit remains flat at Rs 1,310 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: The company's revenue from operations was up 15.69 per cent to Rs 12,016.78 crore during Q2 FY22 as against Rs 10,387.14 crore it registered in the corresponding quarter of previous fiscal.

news.title: Sunteck Realty acquires 110 acres land near Mumbai
news.para: This land will be used for plotted and bungalows development. The project is located close to Pen city and has a development potential of 4-5 million sq ft.

news.title: Goa: Sao Jose de Areal locals oppose land use change
news.para: “No land use change shall be allowed except for individual houses for local residents and indigent citizens and schools, hospitals, markets, jogging parks, playgrounds for locals,” the resolution read.

news.title: Embassy REIT raises Rs 4,600 crore debt to refinancing existing borrowing
news.para: Both these proceeds, totaling Rs 4,600 crore will be used for early refinance of zero-coupon bond (Series I NCDs) which carried an average 9.4% coupon on November 2, 2021. Embassy REIT will be able to secure c.300 basis points interest savings annually through this refinance.

news.title: Punjab CM launches scheme to give property rights to people living within 'lal lakir'
news.para: Punjab chief minister Charanjit Singh Channi said that earlier this scheme was launched only for the residents of villages but now it is being extended to the eligible residents of the cities within the 'lal lakir'.

news.title: Minister tells officials to note demands for rehabilitation of Chikhali, Ambewadi residents
news.para: Satej Patil, the district guardian minister, has instructed the authorities to take note of the villagers’ demands, especially related to the plot requirement for permanent settlement.

news.title: Chandigarh: Rs 1.7 crore plan to turn construction waste plant automatic
news.para: With the engineering department of the MC consulting technical experts for converting the plant, sources said the output of the materials through C&D waste will be more than five to six times than the current scenario.

news.title: BEE to adopt Indo-Swiss technology to construct 28 lakh houses in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The BEEP project is aimed at adopting ‘Indo-Swiss energy efficient building technology’ to promote energy-efficient building design in the construction of the proposed 28 lakh houses in Andhra Pradesh.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Apartments association raises issue of Indirapuram handover to civic body
news.para: T​he letter, with reference to a 1983 government order, says if any municipality starts charging house tax in an area, then it will automatically be deemed to be handed over to the civic body (Ghaziabad Municipal Corporation (GMC)).

news.title: Haryana CM directs HSVP to repair flats in Gurugram's Sector 47
news.para: He also asked the officials to prepare a list of beneficiaries and allot these flats to them within the stipulated time. To rehabilitate slum dwellers, HSVP had constructed a total of 1,088 cheap flats in 2011 and 2015.
